@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Pipeliner' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on any space, occupied or not, the pipe section
that is shown at the right of the game board, under the 'Next' word,
will go where you clicked... If there was a pipe section where you
clicked on, that pipe section will become the next pipe section to
be placed...

  As you complete a pipeline from the starting to end pipe sections,
you get points according to the number of pipe sections which are
part of the pipeline. The higher the number of pipe sections that
are used, the more points you get...

  The game's scoring procedure follows this formulae: the number of
rows (9) plus the number of columns separating the entry and exit
(ranging from 2 to 8) is deducted from the number of pipe sections
you use to complete a pipeline. If the total exceeds zero, then the
number of points you get will be the total multiplied by 2,
otherwise you will get one point. For example: if you use 19 pipe
sections to complete a pipeline and the entry is at the upper left
and the exit is at the lower right, the deduction will be 17
[9 + 8]. The result will be 19 - 17 = 2. That result will then be
multiplied by 2 and the number of points you will get would be 4.

  As the game progress, in addition to normal pipe sections,
'Special' tiles will appear from time to time, just to help or
complicate the gameplay, these tiles are:

-Block:               A block can be placed anywhere and it has no
                      use, except for being there when you do not
                      need it. Once it is placed, it cannot be moved
                      afterwards. Additionally, blocks remain for
                      the rest of the game as they cannot be
                      eliminated, even with an exploding tile.

-Frozen pipe section: This type of pipe section is like any normal
                      pipe sections except that it is inside an
                      'ice cube'. When placed at a location, it
                      cannot move afterwards. If one or more frozen
                      pipe sections are part of a completed
                      pipeline, they will be removed along with the
                      rest of the pipeline's pipe sections.

-Exploding tile:      When clicking at any location, except where a
                      block or frozen pipe is located. That tile
                      will explode and remove pipe sections (normal
                      or frozen) that are immediately next to it.
                      You get 5 points for each pipe section that
                      is eliminated.

-Mystery tile:        This tile is marked by a question mark ('?').
                      When placed, it will reveal a normal or frozen
                      pipe section.

  Just be careful that you do not fill the board completely with
pipe sections or with other tiles, as that would end the game.
Also, avoid at all time placing a block under the entry or above
the exit pipe, as well as any frozen pipe section that is located
next but not oriented toward the entry or exit pipe, as this would
also end the game.

  Have fun!

  To quit the game, click on the game window's close button or
press the 'Esc' key.

